President Trump made remarks at the Kennedy Space Center in Florida after witnessing the launch of the SpaceX Crew Dragon spacecraft. He expressed his pride in NASA and the collaboration between public and private sectors. Trump also mentioned speaking to Elon Musk and praised him as a "great brain." He acknowledged the courage of the astronauts and the danger involved in space travel. Trump also highlighted the revitalization of the space program during his presidency and the future plans to go to Mars and the Moon. He emphasized the economic impact and technological advancements brought about by the space program, as well as the creation of the Space Force. Trump stated that space will be one of the most important endeavors undertaken and compared it to the significance of federal judges and Supreme Court justices.